Barclays May Lose $500 Million on Russia Unit, Vedomosti Reports

-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 
2011-08-03T04:56:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-03/barclays-may-lose-500-million-on-russia-unit-vedomosti-reports.html
Barclays Bank Plc may lose as much as
$500 million on investments in  Russia ,  Vedomosti  reported,
citing bank documents.  Barclays expects 64 million pounds ($104 million) in losses
from the sale of its Russian unit acquired in 2008, the Moscow-
based newspaper said.  The bank already wrote off $392 million in goodwill for the
acquisition of the unit in its 2010 annual report, Vedomosti
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
 ikhrennikov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Viljoen at 
 jviljoen@bloomberg.net  